  "prompt": "What is the formula to calculate a synchronous speed of a motor?",
  "response": "The synchronous speed of a motor, especially in the context of alternating current (AC) induction motors, can be calculated using the following formula:\n\n\\[\nN_s = \\frac{120 \\times f}{P}\n\\]\n\nWhere:\n- \\( N_s \\) = Synchronous speed in revolutions per minute (RPM)\n- \\( f \\) = Frequency of the AC supply in hertz (Hz)\n- \\( P \\) = Number of poles in the motor\n\nThis formula provides the theoretical speed at which the magnetic field rotates in the motor, and it is important for understanding the performance of the motor in relation to its load.",
